tspan.tspan: In the first problem we saw a sudden increase in average
energy and then a slowing down growth which is similar to
a graph of a logarithm. The explanation is that energy in
the Ising model is analagous to entropy because it is
related to how the neighbours are situated around a given
point and because the Boltzmann distribution will always
relax to a distribution with the largest entropy (the most
microstates) the energy will evolve analogously. Due to
this, the number of blobs will increase in the same manner
because the state with the most entropy is the one where
energy between states is averagised so for small
temperatures the state will be more lumpy than for bigger
ones. The third one is based on the same principle with
